                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 (E.W.)/11–742: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers (<persName type="from"
                            >Cole</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">War Department</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="41" xml:id="d420fn41">Copy supplied by the Office of the Secretary of
                        Defense under cover of letter of September 7, 1960.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-04">November 4,
                            1942</date>.]<lb/>[Received November 5—4 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. 757. [From Murphy.] Your M–20, 27th, paragraph 3. In view of message received
                    this morning from Kingpin regarding his decision to proceed North Africa I am
                    informing Flagpole this afternoon on assault date and name of
                    commander-in-chief. To avoid error please confirm assault date. [Murphy.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
